  ANIMALS OF THE WORLD
============================================================

Name:         Tardigrade
Scientific:   Ramazzottius varieornatus
Class:        Tardigrada
Habitat:      Everywhere
Diet:         Omnivore
Lifespan:     2.5 years
Weight:       1e-07 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Nearly indestructible; survives space vacuum, radiation, extreme temps

Name:         Axolotl
Scientific:   Ambystoma mexicanum
Class:        Amphibia
Habitat:      Lakes
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     15 years
Weight:       0.3 kg
Status:       Critically Endangered
Fact:         Can regenerate entire limbs, spine, heart, and brain tissue

Name:         Bowhead Whale
Scientific:   Balaena mysticetus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Arctic ocean
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     200 years
Weight:       100000 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Longest-lived mammal at 200+ years; can break 60cm of ice

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

Theorem/Law:  Euler Polyhedron Formula
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      V - E + F = 2
Applications: Architecture, crystallography
Discoverer:   Leonhard Euler (1758)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

